&lt;p&gt;Rapid Response Service Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harrow Rapid Response is an award winning , well established and expanding admissions avoidance service working with both the primary care and acute sectors to support and deliver treatment to patients at home. We are currently looking for a motivated and committed team leader to continue to drive the ongoing development of the service and team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be experienced practitioners with sound clinical knowledge and proven experience in acute and community clinical environments. Alongside this you will need to have evidence of strong leadership to drive the teams performance. You will need to be adaptable to operate in an ever changing environment. Candidates should have excellent communication skills and the ability to communicate at a strategic level. You need to have the ability and drive to support the team in an ever changing health environment.&lt;/p&gt;
